        "created_at": "2026-01-15T04:35:05.329Z",
        "cooked": "<p>A friend asked about if the Android app can be modified to be truly black instead of just dark gray. They suffer from a severe case of ME/CFS, which comes with extreme light sensitivity in their case. A true black theme would simplify communication a lot, they say.</p>\n<p>Now before going ahead and modifying the app myself, I checked for existing feature requests (and even <a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Android/pull/8466\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">a pull request</a>), all of which were declined because “2 themes are enough” or because the Material Design guidelines say so - but all from a UI point of view. The fact that a AMOLED/black theme could be an accessibility feature isn’t mentioned anywhere.</p>\n<p>So, would you please reconsider?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
        "updated_at": "2026-01-15T04:35:05.329Z",
