        "created_at": "2026-01-15T16:54:06.193Z",
        "cooked": "<p>assuming it’s the same friend as the thread i saw, i must say i never considered AMOLED themes to be an accessibility issue, but of course now that it has been brought to my attention i am even more supportive of this FR.<br>\ni will say that i’m on the fence on merging this thread with the existing thread, since of course this is talking about accessibility and the other one is talking about power saving and aesthetics.</p><aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"4571\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/1/d/1de927662cdb67f55ff2517297de9326187912be.png\" data-download-href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/1de927662cdb67f55ff2517297de9326187912be\" title=\"\"><img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/1/d/1de927662cdb67f55ff2517297de9326187912be.png\" class=\"avatar\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\"></span><span class=\"informations\">120×120 1.75 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div>\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/pure-black-background-as-dark-theme-amoled/4571\">Pure black background as \"dark theme\" (AMOLED)</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/ux/android-ux-ui/30\"><span data-category-id=\"30\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #B01C2A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #FF4242;\" data-parent-category-id=\"28\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square --has-parent\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Android UI/UX</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    The latest updates made the dark theme more of a grey which kinda kills a lot of the whole amoled power savings idea. \nCan we either have the “dark theme” be black again or have a third option for “black theme”? \nThanks, love the app!\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
