        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/e47774/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-15T17:19:10.557Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-top_contributors\" data-username=\"rassilon1963\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"74234\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/48/31625_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> rassilon1963:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>this is talking about accessibility and the other one is talking about power saving and aesthetics.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Exactly, that’s why i created this thread. It being merged with another one, where accessibility is hardly (if at all) mentioned would really erase this being an accessibility issue for some people. And from what I’ve seen, the Signal team has rejected the request for an “AMOLED”/true black theme for both an aesthetic and a power saving perspective.</p>\n<p>Someone asking for this feature from an accessibility perspective is a completed different thing, and implies a very different conservation to be had around it.</p>",
